 more importantly, of having a common advertising platform, while ensuring =
that Disney keeps the upside of that linkage (which will be realized in ad =
revenue on its non-sports services). In that sense I=E2=80=99m actually not=
 sure how valuable a partnership would be for either tech companies or spor=
ts leagues, even if the allure for Disney is clear. Iger said:

We believe we have an opportunity there as we bring it in the direct-to-con=
sumer direction. To strengthen our hand when we do that by partnering with =
either tech companies that can provide us with marketing technology support=
, customer acquisition help, or sports leagues that can provide us with mor=
e content. It=E2=80=99s that simple. We are actually quite bullish about it=
.

I=E2=80=99m sure they are, if my read of the situation is right, but then w=
ho wants to be a partner in a break-even service that makes Disney=E2=80=99=
s other services richer? There are still some options: Apple/Meta for a com=
mitted VR partner, or Apple/Amazon/Google if they wanted to build the ultim=
ate sports guide ( https://stratechery.com/2023/an-espn-aggregator-google-m=
agic-eraser-bing-chat-monetization/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtp=
ZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdWQiOiJzdH=
JhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJhenAiOiJIS0xjUzREd1Nod1AyWURLYmZQV00xI=
iwiZW50Ijp7InVyaSI6WyJodHRwczovL3N0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LmNvbS8yMDIzL2FuLWVzcG4tYWdn=
cmVnYXRvci1nb29nbGUtbWFnaWMtZXJhc2VyLWJpbmctY2hhdC1tb25ldGl6YXRpb24vIl19LCJ=
