Q7inWy7QyrKa6dPIoe1D1RaerfKqQGRN_-au36gNC-0Vq5yt1zcoScDE7YhEviGWjIOSC09yRg =
). On the league side the NBA has a bunch of local rights coming back from =
Bally ( https://www.sportsbusinessjournal.com/SB-Blogs/Newsletter-Media/202=
3/11/06.aspx ) that could both provide useful content for ESPN+ and which t=
hey need help selling and monetizing.

Iger was very clear, though, that ESPN isn=E2=80=99t taking on sports right=
s willy-nilly; in response to a question about local rights specifically he=
 said:

Regarding local sports, the technology that we will have for ESPN DTC will =
give us the ability to provide local sports in a pretty robust way, basical=
ly what the RSNs are doing. But we=E2=80=99re not really aiming to do so by=
 taking on significant risk. So if we can find the right kind of business a=
rrangements and partnerships, I think we=E2=80=99ll look very seriously at =
providing local sports as part of that platform. But again, not if it resul=
ts in us taking on too much risk.

This is the reality of streaming: either content moves the needle, driving =
customer acquisition and reducing churn, or it is simply a cost center; Dis=
ney is determined to avoid the latter going forward, in every aspect of its=
 business, and I think it=E2=80=99s a plan, both on this point and broadly =
speaking, that makes sense.

